  "translations": {
    "en": "And the right of the one who trains you through knowledge is magnifying him, respecting his sessions, listening well and attending devotedly. Do not raise your voice toward him nor answer anyone who asks him, let him answer. Do not speak to anyone or backbite in his session. Defend him when ill-spoken of, conceal his faults, manifest his virtues. Do not sit with his enemy or oppose his friend. If you do this, Allah's angels will testify that you went to him and learned for Allah's sake, not for people.",
